The other thing I should mention is that Canadian vehicles have to be imported through US Customs before they can be registered.

http://www.nhtsa.dot.gov/cars/rules/import/

The customs officer will fill out an HS-7 Declaration Form and you will declare that the vehicle is 25 years or older. Check box #1 only.

http://www.customslink.com/forms_printable/form_hs7.pdf

